## MCP Server

Exposes the Digital Therapy Assistant as an MCP server for AI clients like Claude Desktop via stdio transport.

### Setup

```bash
mvn package -DskipTests
```

Copy `claude_desktop_config.json` from the project root to `~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json` (Mac) or `%APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json` (Windows), update the absolute JAR path and Anthropic API key, then restart Claude Desktop.

### Testing

```bash
npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector java -jar target/digitaltherapy-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar --spring.profiles.active=mcp
```

### Available Tools
`start_session`, `chat_in_session`, `end_session`, `get_session_library`, `get_session_history`, `create_diary_entry`, `analyze_thought`, `suggest_reframing`, `detect_crisis`, `get_coping_strategies`, `get_weekly_progress`, `get_insights`

### Available Resources
`therapy://crisis/resources`, `therapy://distortions`, `therapy://sessions/{sessionId}`, `therapy://diary/{userId}`, `therapy://diary/entry/{entryId}`, `therapy://progress/{userId}`, `therapy://safetyplan/{userId}`

### Available Prompts
`thought_analysis`, `session_summary`, `weekly_check_in`